            . I apprehended her on the 22d of August, she said she had pawned the watch in Shoreditch. I named a shop at the corner of an alley - she said she had pawned it there for 25 s., in the name of Anderson, and I found it next day in pawn, in Turnmill-street, in the name of Lawson.</p>
